==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heulandite
<hw>Heu"land*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[After
<ets>Heuland</ets>, an English mineralogist.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A mineral of the Zeolite family, often occurring in amygdaloid, in
foliated masses, and also in monoclinic crystals with pearly luster on
the cleavage face. It is a hydrous silicate of alumina and
lime.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

